370
00:36:58,545 --> 00:36:59,838
No, I'm not.

371
00:37:00,881 --> 00:37:02,841
It was just never anything that interested me.

372
00:37:02,841 --> 00:37:03,675
Well, you're awfully

373
00:37:03,717 --> 00:37:04,968
modern aren't you?

374
00:37:05,552 --> 00:37:07,971
You know, I think that was the first thing that I noticed about you...

375
00:37:10,056 --> 00:37:11,975
...was how sure of yourself you were.

376
00:37:14,978 --> 00:37:17,355
How can you be so sure about everything at your age?

377
00:37:18,857 --> 00:37:20,650
You think I'm sure of myself?

378
00:37:21,485 --> 00:37:22,486
Of course, you are.

379
00:37:45,133 --> 00:37:46,676
I'm finished now. Thank you.

380
00:37:52,849 --> 00:37:54,100
Yes, Mr. Falconer?

381
00:37:55,352 --> 00:37:57,270
Is there something else we can help you with today?

382
00:37:57,270 --> 00:37:59,981
I can't find my check book and I need some cash.

383
00:38:00,857 --> 00:38:03,485
Not my day I'm afraid. Excuse me a minute.

384
00:38:57,414 --> 00:39:00,250
Mommy says bushy eyebrows are pedestrian,

385
00:39:00,250 --> 00:39:01,668
but I think yours are pretty.

386
00:39:02,794 --> 00:39:04,671
I think yours are pretty too.

387
00:39:05,172 --> 00:39:06,840
Why do you look so sad?

388
00:39:06,840 --> 00:39:09,050
Would you like to meet Charlton Heston?

389
00:39:10,886 --> 00:39:11,887
Ben Hur.

390
00:39:14,556 --> 00:39:15,974
He's our scorpion.

391
00:39:16,850 --> 00:39:20,187
Every night we throw in something new to him and watch him kill it.

392
00:39:20,645 --> 00:39:22,606
Daddy says it's like the colosseum.

393
00:39:22,606 --> 00:39:25,358
So my brother Tom put on all the columns in here.

394
00:39:26,067 --> 00:39:27,819
He wants to be a set designer.

395
00:39:28,361 --> 00:39:30,030
He hasn't eaten the spider yet...

396
00:39:30,030 --> 00:39:33,033
...cause he's still full from the moth we gave him last night.

397
00:39:33,700 --> 00:39:36,453
Daddy says he wants to throw you in to the colosseum.

398
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:39,456
No kidding? Why?

399
00:39:40,040 --> 00:39:41,666
He says you're light in your loafers...

400
00:39:41,708 --> 00:39:44,127
...but you aren't even wearing loafers.

401
00:39:44,169 --> 00:39:46,713
I think my brother Tom is light in his loafers too...

402
00:39:46,713 --> 00:39:49,299
...but he wears Keds.

403
00:39:50,509 --> 00:39:55,347
He made me do a hair conditioning treatment on my hair with eggs.

404
00:39:55,972 --> 00:39:57,390
Does it look shiny?

405
00:39:58,141 --> 00:40:00,227
Sweetheart, what are you doing bothering Mr. Falconer?

406
00:40:00,227 --> 00:40:03,522
She's not bothering me at all Susan. How are you?

407
00:40:03,730 --> 00:40:05,732
I'm glad to see you George.

408
00:40:06,858 --> 00:40:09,069
George, we're having a few people over tonight for drinks...

409
00:40:09,110 --> 00:40:11,154
...and would love to have you join us if you could.

410
00:40:11,154 --> 00:40:13,406
Thank you. That's very kind of you but I have plans.

411
00:40:14,616 --> 00:40:15,992
Another time then.

412
00:40:16,910 --> 00:40:19,204
Jennifer, let's let Mr. Falconer get back to his banking.

413
00:40:19,204 --> 00:40:20,205
Goodbye, George.

414
00:40:20,205 --> 00:40:22,290
Bye, Susan. Bye, Jennifer.

415
00:40:31,716 --> 00:40:33,009
May I help you, sir?

416
00:40:33,593 --> 00:40:35,762
I'd like to buy some bullets for this gun, please.

417
00:40:35,762 --> 00:40:39,432
Yes, sir. This is a really old gun, sir.

418
00:40:39,432 --> 00:40:41,601
We have a two for one sale on handguns at the moment.

419
00:40:41,601 --> 00:40:43,144
Perhaps one for the little lady?

420
00:40:43,186 --> 00:40:44,813
No thank you. Just the bullets, please.

421
00:40:48,066 --> 00:40:49,568
Here you go. Anything else?

422
00:40:50,110 --> 00:40:50,986
No, thank you.

423
00:40:51,027 --> 00:40:52,696
That would be $2.29, sir.

424
00:40:56,533 --> 00:40:57,242
Thank you.

425
00:41:35,363 --> 00:41:38,241
I'm sorry. I hope she didn't growl at you.

426
00:41:38,241 --> 00:41:40,911
She goes a little crazy sometimes when I have to leave her in the car.

427
00:41:40,911 --> 00:41:42,496
She's perfect. What's her name?

428
00:41:42,704 --> 00:41:43,663
India.

429
00:41:44,581 --> 00:41:45,457
Let's go there.

430
00:41:50,962 --> 00:41:51,922
You little baby.

431
00:41:56,009 --> 00:41:59,846
I used to have smooth fox terriers. You don't see them very often.

432
00:42:21,201 --> 00:42:23,119
The very smell of buttered toast.

433
00:42:24,329 --> 00:42:25,622
She's still a puppy isn't she?

434
00:42:32,045 --> 00:42:33,004
Well.

435
00:42:33,004 --> 00:42:35,131
Have a nice evening.        You too.

436
00:42:35,799 --> 00:42:36,842
Good night, India.

437
00:42:50,355 --> 00:42:51,982
I'm sorry about that.        No, It's ok.

438
00:42:53,483 --> 00:42:55,152
It's my fault. I'll get you another pack.

439
00:42:55,485 --> 00:42:56,653
It's ok. Don't worry.

440
00:42:57,821 --> 00:42:59,030
No, no I insist.

441
00:43:04,161 --> 00:43:04,995
Thank you.

442
00:43:05,829 --> 00:43:07,205
I'm sorry about the broken glass.

443
00:43:07,956 --> 00:43:09,708
Here you go.        Thanks man.

444
00:43:12,043 --> 00:43:12,919
You want one?

445
00:43:14,087 --> 00:43:14,754
No, thanks.

446
00:43:16,965 --> 00:43:19,050
Actually, yes. Why not?

447
00:43:19,759 --> 00:43:20,468
Thank you.

448
00:43:52,417 --> 00:43:54,252
Carlos.        What did you say?

449
00:43:54,252 --> 00:43:56,880
Carlos. You asked me my name.

450
00:43:56,880 --> 00:43:58,048
Are you okay?

451
00:44:00,217 --> 00:44:00,967
Yeah.

452
00:44:01,968 --> 00:44:02,802
Yeah, I'm sorry.

453
00:44:07,265 --> 00:44:09,100
You're really something.

454
00:44:09,684 --> 00:44:10,977
You have an incredible face.

455
00:44:11,811 --> 00:44:13,647
Enjoy that. It's a great gift.

456
00:44:14,648 --> 00:44:16,024
Your Spanish is perfect.

457
00:44:16,024 --> 00:44:16,858
Thank you.

458
00:44:20,987 --> 00:44:22,614
I should have used it more.

459
00:44:23,782 --> 00:44:24,491
Well...

460
00:44:25,116 --> 00:44:26,034
It's not too late.

461
00:44:54,312 --> 00:44:55,272
What are you doing?

462
00:44:56,523 --> 00:44:57,899
Aren't we going somewhere?

463
00:44:59,109 --> 00:45:02,028
No. But, thanks.

464
00:45:07,159 --> 00:45:07,784
You know, it's the smog

465
00:45:07,784 --> 00:45:09,286
that makes it that color.

466
00:45:10,412 --> 00:45:12,622
I've never seen a sky like this before.

467
00:45:14,249 --> 00:45:17,377
Sometimes awful things have their own kind of beauty.

468
00:45:22,924 --> 00:45:24,634
Could I have another cigarette?

469
00:45:25,093 --> 00:45:26,011
Sure.

470
00:45:54,539 --> 00:45:57,334
Are sure that you don't want to go for a drive?        I'm sure.

471
00:46:00,754 --> 00:46:02,881
Where are you from?        Madrid.

472
00:46:02,881 --> 00:46:05,509
Madrid? How did you get here?

473
00:46:06,134 --> 00:46:07,344
It's a long story.

474
00:46:08,011 --> 00:46:10,305
I met a guy from LA at the hotel where I worked...

475
00:46:10,305 --> 00:46:11,097
...who told me

476
00:46:11,097 --> 00:46:14,684
I could live with him and that he could get me an agent.

477
00:46:14,684 --> 00:46:16,895
But he never realized that I have a Spanish accent.

478
00:46:18,271 --> 00:46:21,858
I like your accent. You speak very well.

479
00:46:23,485 --> 00:46:24,861
How did you learn English?

480
00:46:25,779 --> 00:46:28,532
My mom had an American boyfriend when I was little.

481
00:46:28,657 --> 00:46:30,116
Is your mother in Madrid?

482
00:46:31,201 --> 00:46:33,203
Yes, she is. She cuts hair.

483
00:46:33,203 --> 00:46:35,121
She cut my hair before I left.

484
00:46:35,539 --> 00:46:36,665
Do you like it?

485
00:46:37,874 --> 00:46:39,960
I thought it made me look like James Dean.

486
00:46:39,960 --> 00:46:41,586
You are better than James Dean.

487
00:46:42,295 --> 00:46:43,296
Really?

488
00:46:43,296 --> 00:46:44,214
Thanks.

489
00:46:48,969 --> 00:46:51,763
No one has ever picked me up and not wanted something.

490
00:46:52,347 --> 00:46:53,765
I think you picked me up.

491
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:57,477
This is kind of a serious day for me.

492
00:46:58,353 --> 00:47:01,815
Come on. What could be so serious for a guy like you?

493
00:47:05,068 --> 00:47:07,070
I'm just trying to get over an old love I guess.

494
00:47:09,948 --> 00:47:12,325
My mother says that lovers are like buses.

495
00:47:12,325 --> 00:47:15,829
You just have to wait a little while and another one comes along.

496
00:47:21,960 --> 00:47:22,919
